This paper deals with motion planning for a nonholonomic robot, specifically a quadcopter, in narrow passages. This topic falls under the field of robotics, which is covered by the cs.RO sub-category. The paper also proposes a new algorithm, which involves using RRT and local constraints, which could be considered as artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also mentions using a simulated environment, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
